          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13227395/comment/16818695",
            "id": "16818695",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=Tao+Yang",
              "name": "Tao Yang",
              "key": "tao yang",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Tao Yang",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Shanghai"
            },
            "body": "Hi, [~zhuqi]. \r\nMulti-thread asynchronous scheduling only means support scheduling in multiple threads, scheduling approaches can be classified as node-based and request-based, currently fair scheduler only support node-based and capacity scheduler can support both, global scheduler is request-based and aims for enhancing scheduling performance and considering complex resource placement requirements. \r\nI think your purpose is to support global scheduler including multi-thread asynchronous scheduling, multi-nodes lookup mechanism, placement constraints etc for fair scheduler, Right?",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=Tao+Yang",
              "name": "Tao Yang",
              "key": "tao yang",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Tao Yang",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Shanghai"
            },
            "created": "2019-04-16T06:50:16.633+0000",
            "updated": "2019-04-16T09:51:13.924+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13227395/comment/16819765",
            "id": "16819765",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=zhuqi",
              "name": "zhuqi",
              "key": "zhuqi",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=zhuqi&avatarId=39200",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=zhuqi&avatarId=39200",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=zhuqi&avatarId=39200",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=zhuqi&avatarId=39200"
              },
              "displayName": "Qi Zhu",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
            },
            "body": "Hi,\u00a0[~Tao Yang]\u00a0.\r\n\r\nThanks for your reply.\r\n\r\nYes, i mean the final multi-thread asynchronous scheduling can be supported in\u00a0global scheduler base\u00a0request-based. And the\u00a0non-HB driven approach that continuous scheduling has be removed\u00a0 because of the lock contention in large scale (YARN-6486),\u00a0\u00a0the development of global scheduling for fair scheduler should be a long time . If we can first add a RM service for scheduling performance improvements only, but not consider all the\u00a0complex resource placement requirements, which can be coupled with some simple localilty relaxation strategy?",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=zhuqi",
              "name": "zhuqi",
              "key": "zhuqi",
              "avatarUrls": {
